                                                                                            <p><strong>Lala Mammadova</strong>, from Baku, Azerbaijan, is a double major in English and American studies and general and comparative literature at Ruhr University Bochum. She was an exchange student at the University of Oklahoma, a <em>WLT</em> Student Advisory Board member, and a <em>WLT</em> intern. She enjoys creative writing and aims to pursue a career in writing and publishing.</p>
